Running Dev and Production Servers

* Parcel commands can be added inside package.json scripts.
* npm start or npm run start runs development server.
* npm run build creates production build.
* Scripts make project execution easier and faster.

---

JSX (JavaScript XML)

* JSX allows writing HTML-like syntax inside JavaScript.
* Browsers do not understand JSX directly.
* JSX gets converted into React.createElement.
* It improves readability and developer experience.

---

Babel

* Babel is a JavaScript compiler.
* It converts modern JavaScript into browser-compatible code.
* It also converts JSX into JavaScript objects.
* Conversion flow: JSX → React.createElement → React Element → HTML render.

---

Functional Components

* Functional components are JavaScript functions returning JSX.
* Component names must start with uppercase letters.
* Lowercase names are treated as HTML elements.
* Components can be reused easily.

---

Component Composition

* Using one component inside another component is called composition.
* Helps create complex UI from small components.
* Encourages modular design.

---

JavaScript Expressions in JSX

* Curly braces {} allow JavaScript inside JSX.
* Can include variables, functions, or calculations.
* Helps create dynamic UI content.

---

Script Type Attribute

* Defines the type of script content.
* Common values:

  * text/javascript (default)
  * module (supports import/export)
  * text/babel
  * text/typescript
* module type is required for ES module usage.

---

Component Syntax Differences

* {Title} refers to a variable or function.
* {<Title />} renders a component.
* <Title></Title> and <Title /> are same if no children exist.

---

Config Driven UI

* UI is generated using configuration data like JSON.
* Makes UI dynamic and customizable.
* Reduces hardcoding.

---

Reconciliation in React

* React compares old Virtual DOM with new Virtual DOM.
* Updates only changed parts in Real DOM.
* Improves performance by minimizing DOM operations.

---

React Fiber

* React Fiber is the new core algorithm of React.
* It improves rendering speed and responsiveness.
* Breaks work into smaller units for better scheduling.
* It is an internal architecture improvement.

---

Keys in React

* Keys uniquely identify list elements.
* Help React track changes efficiently.
* Improve rendering performance.
* Keys should be unique among siblings.

---

Using Index as Keys

* Using index as keys is not recommended when list order changes.
* Can cause performance issues and incorrect UI behavior.
* React uses index as default if no key is provided.

---

Exports in JavaScript

* A file can have only one default export.
* A file can have multiple named exports.
* Both can exist in the same file.

---

React Hooks

* Hooks are functions provided by React with built-in logic.
* They allow state and lifecycle features in functional components.
* Hooks simplify component logic.

---

useState Hook

* useState provides state management in functional components.
* Returns state variable and update function.
* Updating state triggers re-render.
* State persists across renders.

---

Diff Algorithm

* React uses a diff algorithm to compare Virtual DOM versions.
* Finds minimal changes needed for updates.
* Reduces expensive DOM operations.

---

Monolithic Architecture

* Entire application is built as one single unit.
* Components are tightly connected.
* Hard to scale and maintain.
* Easier during early development.

---

Microservices Architecture

* Application is divided into independent services.
* Each service has its own logic and database.
* Services can be deployed and scaled separately.
* Improves flexibility and scalability.

---

Fetching Data from API

* Approach 1: Load page → Fetch data → Render UI.
* Approach 2: Load page → Render skeleton → Fetch data → Update UI.
* React usually follows the second approach.

---

fetch() Function

* fetch() is used to request data from network.
* Returns a Promise with response object.
* Promise fails only on network errors.

---

CORS (Cross-Origin Resource Sharing)

* Security mechanism allowing cross-domain requests.
* Browsers block cross-origin requests by default.
* Server must allow access using headers.

---

Shimmer UI

* Shows placeholder layout while data loads.
* Better user experience than loading spinner.
* Improves perceived performance.

---

State Updates with Const

* State variables update through React re-rendering.
* React recreates state with new values internally.
* Even const variables can change through state setter.

---

useEffect Hook

* Handles side effects like API calls and DOM updates.
* Runs after component render.
* Dependency array controls execution:

  * No array → runs every render.
  * Empty array → runs once.
  * With values → runs when dependencies change.
* Replaces lifecycle methods of class components.

